.\" Manpage for incusmgr
.TH man 1 "02 June 2026" "202606040840-git" "incusmgr"

.SH NAME
incusmgr \- Comprehensive Incus container and VM management tool

.SH DESCRIPTION
A self-contained command-line tool for managing Incus containers and virtual machines. Provides lifecycle management, storage pool operations, network configuration, profile management, image operations, snapshot management, and system cleanup utilities.

.SH SYNOPSIS
incusmgr [options] [command] [arguments...]

.SH INSTANCE COMMANDS
.TP
.B list [filter]
List all instances with optional filter
.TP
.B ls [filter]
Alias for list
.TP
.B ps
List running instances only
.TP
.B inactive
List stopped instances only
.TP
.B status [name]
Show instance or overall Incus status
.TP
.B info <name>
Show detailed information about an instance
.TP
.B launch <image> [name]
Create and start an instance
.TP
.B run <image> [name]
Alias for launch
.TP
.B install <image> [name]
Alias for launch
.TP
.B init <image> [name]
Create an instance without starting it
.TP
.B start <name>
Start a stopped instance
.TP
.B stop <name>
Stop a running instance
.TP
.B restart <name>
Restart an instance
.TP
.B delete <name> [--force]
Delete an instance
.TP
.B rm <name> [--force]
Alias for delete
.TP
.B remove <name>
Alias for delete
.TP
.B copy <src> <dst>
Copy/clone an instance
.TP
.B clone <src> <dst>
Alias for copy
.TP
.B rename <old> <new>
Rename an instance
.TP
.B move <src> <dst>
Move an instance (rename or migrate)

.SH INTERACTION COMMANDS
.TP
.B exec <name> [cmd]
Run a command in an instance (default: bash)
.TP
.B enter <name>
Enter instance shell; starts the instance if stopped
.TP
.B shell <name>
Alias for enter
.TP
.B console <name>
Attach to an instance console
.TP
.B log <name>
Show instance log output
.TP
.B logs <name>
Alias for log
.TP
.B update [name]
Update packages inside instance(s); updates all if name is omitted

.SH SNAPSHOT COMMANDS
.TP
.B snapshot <name> [snap]
Create a snapshot of an instance
.TP
.B restore <name> <snap>
Restore an instance from a snapshot
.TP
.B snapshots <name>
List all snapshots for an instance
.TP
.B delsnapshot <name> <snap>
Delete a named snapshot

.SH IMAGE COMMANDS
.TP
.B image list [remote:]
List images; optionally filter by remote (e.g. images:)
.TP
.B image info <image>
Show detailed image information
.TP
.B image delete <fp>
Delete an image by fingerprint
.TP
.B image copy <src> <dst>
Copy an image between remotes

.SH REMOTE COMMANDS
.TP
.B remote list
List configured remotes
.TP
.B remote add <name> <url>
Add a remote Incus server
.TP
.B remote remove <name>
Remove a remote server

.SH NETWORK COMMANDS
.TP
.B network list
List all networks
.TP
.B network show [name]
Show network details (default: incusbr0)
.TP
.B network create <name>
Create a new network
.TP
.B network delete <name>
Delete a network

.SH STORAGE COMMANDS
.TP
.B storage list
List all storage pools
.TP
.B storage show <pool>
Show storage pool information
.TP
.B storage create <pool>
Create a new storage pool
.TP
.B storage delete <pool>
Delete a storage pool
.TP
.B volume list <pool>
List storage volumes in a pool

.SH PROFILE COMMANDS
.TP
.B profile list
List all profiles
.TP
.B profile show <name>
Show profile configuration
.TP
.B profile create <name>
Create a new profile
.TP
.B profile delete <name>
Delete a profile

.SH PROJECT COMMANDS
.TP
.B project list
List all projects
.TP
.B project show [name]
Show project details

.SH MAINTENANCE COMMANDS
.TP
.B init [force]
Initialize Incus environment and generate config file
.TP
.B prune
Delete all instances, storage volumes (all pools), and images
.TP
.B prune instances
Delete all instances (forced)
.TP
.B prune volumes
Delete all storage volumes across all pools
.TP
.B prune images
Delete all cached images
.TP
.B prune all
Alias for bare prune (all resources)
.TP
.B config
Generate or reset the incusmgr configuration file

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-f, \-\-force
Skip confirmation prompts
.TP
.B \-\-no-color
Disable color output (also honors NO_COLOR env var)
.TP
.B \-\-debug
Enable bash -x tracing
.TP
.B \-\-config
Generate/reset config file
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show version
.TP
.B \-\-help
Show help message

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B incusmgr launch images:ubuntu/22.04 mybox
Launch an Ubuntu 22.04 container named mybox
.TP
.B incusmgr enter mybox
Enter mybox with an interactive shell (starts it if stopped)
.TP
.B incusmgr update mybox
Update packages inside mybox
.TP
.B incusmgr snapshot mybox before-upgrade
Create a snapshot named before-upgrade
.TP
.B incusmgr restore mybox before-upgrade
Restore mybox from the before-upgrade snapshot
.TP
.B incusmgr prune --force
Delete all instances, volumes, and images without confirmation
.TP
.B incusmgr storage list
List all storage pools
.TP
.B incusmgr image list images:
List all images from the images: remote
.TP
.B incusmgr remote add myserver https://incus.example.com:8443
Add a remote Incus server

.SH CONFIGURATION
.TP
.B INCUSMGR_INCUS_BIN
Incus binary to use (default: incus)
.TP
.B INCUSMGR_DEFAULT_STORAGE
Default storage pool (default: default)
.TP
.B INCUSMGR_DEFAULT_NETWORK
Default network bridge (default: incusbr0)
.TP
.B INCUSMGR_DEFAULT_PROFILE
Default profile (default: default)
.TP
.B INCUSMGR_REMOTE
Optional remote to prefix all incus commands
.TP
.B INCUSMGR_PROJECT
Optional project to pass to all incus commands

.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/myscripts/incusmgr/settings.conf
User configuration file
.TP
.I ~/.local/log/incusmgr/
Log directory
.TP
.I ~/.cache/incusmgr/
Cache directory

.SH PRUNE BEHAVIOR
The bare \fBprune\fR (and \fBprune all\fR) command follows this sequence:
.PP
1. Force-delete all instances
.PP
2. Delete all volumes in every storage pool
.PP
3. Delete all cached images
.PP
Confirmation is required unless \fB--force\fR is passed.

.SH NOTES
All functions are self-contained — no external library sourcing. The \fB__incus\fR wrapper automatically prepends remote and project arguments when INCUSMGR_REMOTE or INCUSMGR_PROJECT are set.

